node.text:
ESPN Sources: Denver Nuggets G/F Will Barton has declined his $14.7M player option for the 2021-2022 season and will become a free agent. There’s a strong interest between the organization and Barton to negotiate a new deal once free agency opens in August.

The longest tenured Nugget with 7 seasons, Barton is a top priority for Tim Connelly to keep long-term. Barton started 52 games and averaged 12.7 PPG this year. He lost several weeks with a hamstring injury into the start of playoffs, but finished with a 25-point performance vs. Suns in elimination game.

node.text:
Wes Unseld Jr., has agreed to a four-year deal to become the new head coach of the Washington Wizards, sources tell ESPN.

The Wizards offered the job to Denver's associate head coach on Friday, and worked out terms today with his agent @elfussports to complete a formal agreement, sources said.

node.text:
The Washington Wizards are offering Denver Nuggets assistant Wes Unseld, Jr., the franchise’s head coaching job and sides are beginning contract talks on Saturday with an expectation of a deal this weekend, sources tell ESPN.

A deal will tie together a remarkable homecoming: Unseld’s late father, Wes Unseld, is the most important figure in franchise history -- a Hall of Fame player, coach and executive with Washington.
Contract talks are expected to begin on Saturday.

Spurs F Keldon Johnson and center JaVale McGee will replace Bradley Beal and Kevin Love on Team USA's roster for the Olympics, sources tell ESPN. McGee will travel to Las Vegas to join team on Saturday.
Johnson earned significant support and momentum to be added to 12-man Team USA roster because of his performance with the USA Select team and Team USA this week, per sources. He’s well-conditioned — which is an important factor on this team right now — and has developed into a favorite of decision-makers and staff.

node.text:
After spending 10 days in Las Vegas preparing for the Olympics, Cleveland’s Kevin Love is withdrawing from Team USA and won’t travel to Tokyo, his agent tells Jeff Schwartz of @excelbasketball tells ESPN. Love is still returning to full form from a right calf injury that kept him out a significant part of the NBA season.
Schwartz shared a statement from Love to ESPN: “"I am incredibly disappointed to not be heading to Tokyo with Team USA, but you need to be at absolute peak performance to compete at the Olympic level and I am just not there yet."
